# Agent instructions (swg-client-v2)

Guidance for AI agents working in this repository. Read by Claude Code (via `CLAUDE.md` â†’
`@AGENTS.md`), and by Codex / Cursor when consulted in this directory.

## Session startup

Before substantial work, restore context from handoffs:

1. Read [.planning/handoff/README.md](.planning/handoff/README.md) for the active handoff index.
2. Read every handoff file listed there (newest / most relevant first).
3. If the task involves GSD milestone work, also read [.planning/STATE.md](.planning/STATE.md) and 
[.planning/PROJECT.md](.planning/PROJECT.md).

Handoffs live in **`.planning/handoff/`** â€” one markdown file per workstream, updated when context 
would otherwise be lost.

## Project constraints

- **Boot gate:** Changes should leave the client bootable to character select unless the task 
explicitly says otherwise.
- **GSD planning:** Milestone state, phases, and requirements are under `.planning/`.
- **Commits:** Only when the user asks; do not push unless asked.

## Repo & branch model

- **This repo is THE source of truth.** Pure **MSBuild** build (`src/build/win32/swg.sln`) â€” **no 
CMake**.
- **Trunk-based on `master`** (since 2026-06-14; the old `koogie-msvc-cpp20-base` branch was
  FF-merged into master and retired). Commit directly on `master`; do **not** branch-per-phase.
- Remotes: **`origin`** = kennethlong/client-tools (push here) Â· **`koogie`** =
  KoogieKepler/client-tools (Koogie's MSVC-C++20 upstream â€” collaboration done; **never push 
there**).
- **`master` is a LIVE upstream-integration branch** â€” the fork is periodically synced from
  SWG-Source. Always `git fetch` before pushing; expect upstream commits to **merge** in, never
  force-overwrite them.
- Active side branch (do not delete): **`d3d9-fixb-d3dcompile-wip`** â€” parked D3DCompile Fix-B, 
for the x64 port.

## Build

- **MSBuild is not on PATH.** Use the env var set in `.claude/settings.json`: `$env:MSBUILD`
  (PowerShell) / `"$MSBUILD"` (bash) â€” the VS18 BuildTools MSBuild.
- **Must be a VS18 / VS 2026 MSBuild** â€” projects target `PlatformToolset=v145`. VS 2022 fails with
  `MSB8020: build tools for v145 cannot be found`.
- **Run builds from PowerShell, not Git Bash** â€” MSYS mangles `/t:Target` and `/p:Foo=Bar`
  (â†’ `MSB1008`). Bash is fine for greps/git.
- **Always pass `/nodeReuse:false`.** Leftover MSBuild/cl nodes hold output-file locks â†’ silent
  truncation. If builds act weird: `Get-Process MSBuild,cl,link | Stop-Process -Force`.
- **Canonical 5-target build** (renderers + client):
  `Direct3d11;Direct3d9;Direct3d9_ffp;Direct3d9_vsps;SwgClient`. Postbuild auto-copies
  `gl0X_d.dll` + `SwgClient_*.exe` into `stage/`.
- **Force a relink** when the exe is up-to-date (so link gates actually run):
  `Remove-Item src\compile\win32\SwgClient\<cfg>\SwgClient_*.exe` before building.
- **Exit 0 â‰  clean link.** SwgClient links under `/FORCE`, which downgrades `unresolved external
  symbol` (LNK2019/2001) to warnings and still emits a binary. **Grep the build log for
  `unresolved external symbol` (must be 0).** (`LNK1181 cannot open input file` is a hard error, not 
masked.)
- **Shared-header ABI trap:** changing a public struct in a shared header (e.g. 
`ShaderImplementation.h`)
  silently breaks ABI with stale plugin DLLs â†’ deterministic boot crash. If you touch a shared
  header consumed by the plugins, **rebuild ALL plugin .vcxprojs** (gl05/06/07/11), not just 
SwgClient.
  Detect: `stat -c %y stage/gl11_d.dll stage/SwgClient_d.exe` â€” dll older than exe + shared-header 
touched = cascade pending.
- Editor tools (AnimationEditor/ParticleEditor/SwgGodClient/etc.) are **pre-broken** on Qt `.ui`
  custom-build (MSB8066). Validation bar = `/t:SwgClient` clean + dual-renderer boot, **not** a 
green full-solution build.

## Run / renderer switch

- **`rasterMajor`** (in the active `.cfg`) selects the renderer plugin DLL, **not** the DirectX
  version. Supported: **`5`** gl05 (D3D9 default) Â· **`6`** gl06 (D3D9 FFP) Â· **`7`** gl07
  (D3D9 VS/PS) Â· **`11`** gl11 (D3D11). **`9` is FATAL** (Graphics.cpp:223) â€” DX9 is value `5`.
- **Which exe reads which cfg:** `SwgClient_d.exe` (Debug) â†’ **`client_d.cfg`** Â·
  `SwgClient_r.exe` (Release) â†’ **`client.cfg`**. Editing the wrong one is silently ignored.
- On a D3D9â†”D3D11 switch, set `rasterMajor` yourself and confirm exe + cfg + rasterMajor + DLL all
  line up **before** declaring a verify. (Reversible local toggle â€” just do it.)

## Config (.cfg) safety

- **Never write `.cfg` with PowerShell `Set-Content` / `Out-File`** â€” PS 5.1 adds a UTF-8 BOM, 
which
  **crashes the Release client at boot** (Debug masks it). Signature: `SwgClient_r.exe` won't start,
  26-byte `(null)-unknown.*.txt` dump, AV in `ConfigFile::Section::getName`.
- Diagnose: `head -c 8 stage/client.cfg | xxd` â€” clean starts `23 20` (`# `), bad starts `ef bb 
bf`.
- Fix: `tail -c +4 client.cfg > tmp && mv tmp client.cfg`. The Edit/Write tools and bash are 
BOM-safe.
- `stage/*.cfg` is gitignored (local dev state); `client.cfg` and `client_d.cfg` are kept in sync 
manually.

## Diagnostics (RenderDoc)

- **RenderDoc D3D9-vs-D3D11 capture-and-diff is THE diagnostic** for render bugs â€” it beats AI
  consensus. RenderDoc **cannot capture D3D9**; capture D3D11 (`gl11`) and diff against D3D9 
reference behavior.
- CLI (no restart needed): `renderdoc-cli.exe <cap.rdc> <cmd>` at
  `D:\Code\renderdoc-mcp\v0.3.0\renderdoc-mcp-windows-x64-v0.3.0\bin\` â€” `info`, `events`,
  `draws [--filter]`, `pipeline -e EID`, `shader vs|ps -e EID`, `pixel X Y -e EID`,
  `debug pixel X Y -e EID --trace` (traces PS â†’ which constant drives a value), `mesh`, 
`export-rt`,
  `capture EXE -o PATH`. The `renderdoc-mcp` MCP server (project `.mcp.json`) exposes the same after 
a Claude Code restart.

## Key paths

| What | Where |
| --- | --- |
| Runtime install (exe, gl0X DLLs, cfgs) | `stage/` â€” builds auto-deploy here |
| Game data (TRE/TOC the client loads) | `D:\Code\SWGSource Client v3.0\` (cfg searchPath points 
here) |
| TRE parser (version-aware, stdlib) | `D:\Code\swg-blender-plugin\swg_pipeline\tre_reader.py` (+ 
`tre_decrypt.py`) |
| Standalone TRE compare tool | `tools/tre-compare/` â€” isolated `uv` package, zero engine imports |
| Audio codec redist (not in git) | `stage/miles/` â€” if audio half-dies / warning-flood lag 
returns, check this first |
| SWG Blender IFF pipeline | **relocated** to `D:\Code\swg-blender-plugin` (was 
`tools/swg_blender/`; left this repo 2026-06-12) |
| MayaExporter / asset parity | `docs/research/maya-exporter-parity-checklist.md` |
| Engine / client code | `src/engine/` |

## Working conventions

- **Don't modify Koogie's source-level changes** without strong reason â€” fix the caller or the 
data,
  not Koogie's diagnostic patches.
- **Just do reversible local changes** in the loop (config edits, `stage/` toggles, file flips) â€” 
don't wait for sign-off.
- **Builds/boots/renders are truth**, not planning docs â€” treat GSD artifacts as lagging reality; 
don't chase artifact drift.
- **Gate close-out commits on an exact staged set** in a dirty repo â€” a chained `git commit -a` can
  sweep unrelated WIP. Stage explicit paths.
- Prefer matching existing code style and minimizing diff scope. Use `gh` for issues/PRs when 
requested.


