<threat_model>
## Trust Boundaries

| Boundary | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| TRE archive -> IncludeHandler -> D3DAssemble | `//asm` `.vsh` + `.inc` source loaded from local 
TRE archives crosses into the assembler. Trusted local build-time game assets (TreeFile-loaded), not 
attacker-controlled. No new external attack surface. |

## STRIDE Threat Register

| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
| T-33-04 | DoS (fail-safe) | D3DAssemble failure / null fn pointer -> silently-nulled VS | mitigate 
| On a null GetProcAddress result or a D3DAssemble error HRESULT, report loudly (FATAL + error blob) 
and do NOT substitute a null VS (D-06: no skipped draws) â€” Task 1 acceptance greps the failure 
branch |
| T-33-05 | Information Disclosure | Include-path traversal in the shared IncludeHandler | accept | 
Reuses the TreeFile-routed handler from the HLSL path â€” no Win32 FS / `..` traversal honored; 
unchanged from the shipped 32-bit behavior |

All other ASVS categories (V2 auth, V3 session, V4 access, V6 crypto) are N/A â€” offline desktop 
renderer, no network/auth/session/crypto surface (33-RESEARCH.md Security Domain).
</threat_model>

