.planning\phases\32-d3dx-to-d3dcompiler-47\32-02-PLAN.md:28:    - "The HLSL //hlsl .vsh compile path 
calls D3DCompile (d3dcompiler_47) via the ABI-identical reinterpret-cast at the call boundary (:477 
call site), with D3DCOMPILE_ENABLE_BACKWARDS_COMPATIBILITY but explicitly WITHOUT 
D3DCOMPILE_PACK_MATRIX_ROW_MAJOR (the D3D9 path uses explicit transposed uploads, not a row-major 
cbuffer contract), NOT D3DXCompileShader; the rejected Restoration redist-d3dx9 shortcut is 
explicitly NOT taken (D-01)"
.planning\phases\32-d3dx-to-d3dcompiler-47\32-02-PLAN.md:29:    - "The vs_1_1 target branch 
(Direct3d9_VertexShaderData.cpp:392-395) is handled explicitly — D3DCompile dropped vs_1_1 support, 
so the path asserts getShaderCapability() >= 2.0 (or promotes to vs_2_0 unconditionally) so a <2.0 
machine can never compile-FATAL or silently null a VS (D-06)"
.planning\phases\32-d3dx-to-d3dcompiler-47\32-02-PLAN.md:30:    - "The v# INPUT-SIGNATURE 
(vertex-input register map) survives the rewrite UNCHANGED vs the D3DX baseline — review-confirmed 
gap (Cursor C1, orchestrator-CONFIRMED): Rules B/C strip the struct-member ': register(v0/v3/v5/v7)' 
SWG authored to match the GAPPED Direct3d9_VertexShaderVertexRegisters.h layout (VSVR_position=0, 
VSVR_normal=3, VSVR_color0=5, VSVR_textureCoordinateSet0=7 — encoded into the shader data files per 
the header's triple WARNING). Task 2(G) MUST disassemble tfcl.vsh + one non-override //hlsl .vsh 
post-D3DCompile and PROVE the input dcl signature is `dcl_position v0, dcl_normal v3, dcl_color v5, 
dcl_texcoord v7` (matching VSVR_*), diffed against the D3DXCompileShader baseline blob — if 
D3DCompile packs sequentially (v0/v1/v2/v3) instead of honoring the gapped map, the bytecode 
disagrees with the D3DVERTEXELEMENT9 decl while still linking = compiles-renders-garbage. This is 
exactly where the WIP branch stalled (D-06)"
