.planning\phases\32-d3dx-to-d3dcompiler-47\32-REVIEWS.md:160:- **[HIGH] PASS gate's coverage basis 
cannot prove "all //asm shaders assemble" — only "the probed subset does."** 32-01 probes 3 baseline 
+ a Task-1 flag-list enumerated over the **16 extracted** `.vsh` (11 //asm), not the 
**286-shader/96-//asm full corpus**, and the flag-list is generated by the same agent eyeballing 
"uncovered constructs." A //asm shader in the unextracted 85 using a rejected construct would PASS 
the gate and only fail at 32-03's render-smoke — **and there is no defined behavior for "gate said 
PASS, 32-03 render-smoke then fails."** The binary gate has no representation for partial-PASS.
