122:1. **Miles stub (#if _M_X64):** Guard the Miles `AIL_*` usage so clientAudio compiles + links 
x64 with no reference to the x86 Mss32 import. The cleanest minimal-diff approach: at each AIL_* 
call site (or, better, wrap the bodies of the functions that call AIL_* — the audio-init, 
sample-play, 3D-position, room-type paths) under `#if _M_X64` provide a no-op / return-success stub 
and `#else` keep the real 7.2e calls. Where a function must return a handle/HRESULT, return a benign 
success/no-op value so callers do not DEBUG_FATAL. The goal: ZERO `AIL_*` symbol reference survives 
in the x64 TU (so no Mss32.lib is needed) AND the client boots SILENT (audio dead, no warning-flood, 
no FATAL). Do NOT lift Restoration's mss64.dll; do NOT link 9.3b — the real port is Phase 35. Add a 
`// Phase 35: Miles 9.3b port (D:\Code\milesss-v9.3b\win\sdk\)` marker comment at the stub boundary. 
The 32-bit (`#else`) path is byte-unchanged (non-regression — clientAudio on 7.2e for Win32 is 
untouched).
